## Process and Team Changes

### Code coverage

The Errata Tool team continues to gradually improve code coverage by requiring
all new features and bugfixes to be accompanied by an autotest.  Additionally,
an effort was made to identify and remove unused code during the 3.11.8
development cycle.

Since Errata Tool 3.11.7, total coverage has improved from 92.65% to 93.51%.

[![Rcov coverage report](images/3.11.8/rcov.png)](images/3.11.8/rcov.png)

What's Next
------------

### Errata Tool 3.11.z

The team will continue to select bugs and RFEs flagged as errata-3.11
in Bugzilla for inclusion in two week sprints. Once enough content is
verified and ready to ship we will do an end-of-sprint release. The
next release in this series will be 3.11.9.

To see current work in progress take a look at the [scrum board in
JIRA][scrumboard].

To see what's currently scheduled for ET 3.11 take a look at [bugs flagged with
errata-3.11 in Bugzilla][bugs_this] or the [Errata Tool Road Map][roadmap].

### Errata Tool 3.12

